The Risk Advisory Services (RAS) Analytics and Innovation Managing Director develops and executes a strategy for innovation, as well as works on RAS Operational and Financial Due Diligence. This role works closely with other leaders within the RAS practice, as well as those across functional groups/regions/markets, to drive collaboration, coaching and training related to strategic initiatives, efficiency, especially as it relates to big data, and innovation.
 
 
The Managing Director handles engagements with big data and brings efficiencies and insights to RAS engagements. This role works closely with the RAS practices to bring solutions to big data challenges and continuously provide improvements to enhance efficiency and promote innovation within the practice.
 
 
The Managing Director plans, oversees and manages detailed project initiatives around the execution of innovation, including how to transform testing methodologies, enhance client deliverables, efficiently and effectively handle big data and train the Firmâ€™s RAS professionals with the skillset to execute the use of tools to promote these initiatives.
 
 
The Managing Director also assists in the development and tactical execution of the RAS strategic plan. This role works closely with RAS and Advisory Leadership to develop, execute and communicate the strategy to achieve the practice and Firmâ€™s vision and core purpose. 
